<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About KitchenAid appliance repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">KitchenAid is Whirlpool's premium kitchen tier, the platform that makes service efficient and the stand mixer category that nobody else fully services.</h2>

    <p>KitchenAid is owned by <strong>Whirlpool Corporation</strong>, the largest major-appliance manufacturer in the world (headquartered in Benton Harbor, Michigan). Within the Whirlpool family, KitchenAid is the premium kitchen-appliance positioning, sitting above standard Whirlpool, alongside Maytag, and below JennAir's ultra-premium tier. KitchenAid focuses on <strong>refrigerators, dishwashers, ranges, wall ovens, cooktops, and stand mixers</strong>. One important accuracy note: <strong>KitchenAid does not make laundry appliances for the US market</strong>, if you need a washer or dryer, that's Whirlpool, Maytag, or one of the other Whirlpool family brands; we cover those separately.</p>

    <p>The Whirlpool Corporation ownership shapes how we approach service. Many KitchenAid refrigerators, dishwashers, and ranges share platforms and parts at the part-number level with Whirlpool models from the same generation, same compressor, same defrost system, same ice maker assembly, with different cosmetic trim and control panels. Our trucks already carry the common Whirlpool platform wear items, which means most KitchenAid service calls in the standard product line get first-visit completion. Where KitchenAid diverges is the premium tier, built-in refrigerators, professional KFGC and KFDC ranges, double wall ovens, and the entire stand mixer category, those use KitchenAid-specific components from authorized distribution.</p>

    <p>Two distinct realities define our KitchenAid service mix. First, the <strong>2018-2021 wire-harness class action</strong> covering Whirlpool, Maytag, KitchenAid, and JennAir Side-by-Side and French Door refrigerators, settlement deadline November 2, 2026. We help homeowners verify eligibility on diagnostic before paying out-of-pocket. Second, the <strong>stand mixer service angle</strong>, KitchenAid stand mixers (Artisan, Professional, Pro Line) are 15+ year kitchen anchors that are absolutely worth keeping running, and we're one of the few shops in LA that actually services them rather than referring them out.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 REFRIGERATOR -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, KitchenAid refrigerator repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">KitchenAid refrigerators, counter-depth French Door, Side-by-Side, and built-in luxury.</h2>

    <p class="lead">KitchenAid refrigerators are some of our higher-volume service in the Whirlpool family across renovation kitchens. The platform splits cleanly: counter-depth standalone units share the Whirlpool family service tree; built-in 42-inch and 48-inch French Door units are premium-tier with sealed-system complexity.</p>

    <p>Most-frequent KitchenAid refrigerator models in our service mix: <strong>KRFF507EWH</strong> and <strong>KRFF507HPS</strong> (36-inch counter-depth French Door, 25 cu ft, white/stainless variants), <strong>KRSC500ESS</strong> (Side-by-Side, 22 cu ft), <strong>KRMF706ESS</strong> (counter-depth French Door with Preserva food care system, 25 cu ft), <strong>KRMF606EBS</strong> (similar Preserva platform in black stainless). Built-in tier: <strong>KBFN502ESS</strong> and <strong>KBFN506ESS</strong> (42-inch and 48-inch French Door built-ins).</p>

    <p>Service tree by year:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 2-5:</strong> ice maker first failure (assembly + dispenser components), water filter housing leaks, door alarm sensor.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5-9:</strong> water inlet valve, evaporator fan motor, condenser fan motor, defrost heater + thermostat, ice maker repeat failures. Wire-harness class action eligibility window for 2018-2021 manufacture units.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 8-12:</strong> compressor service (verify Whirlpool's published warranty on inverter compressors before authorizing out-of-pocket), main control board, sealed-system service on built-in tier.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 12+:</strong> door gasket replacement (especially on built-in tier where heavy doors stress the gasket), full sealed-system service on counter-depth, evaporator coil corrosion in coastal homes.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>We carry common KitchenAid refrigerator parts on the truck, door gaskets, ice maker assemblies, water inlet valves, evaporator fan motors, defrost heaters and thermostats, for first-visit completion on the most common service calls.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 DISHWASHER -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">03, KitchenAid dishwasher repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">KitchenAid dishwashers, KDTM, KDFE, KDPM with 6th Sense detection.</h2>

    <p>KitchenAid dishwashers occupy the premium-tier kitchen builder spec across renovation work in our service area. Models like KDTM354DSS, KDFE104HPS, and KDPM704KPS use the Whirlpool platform underneath with KitchenAid's premium control architecture and 6th Sense soil detection on top. Common service items:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Drain pump failure (year 6-10):</strong> $245-$385 with labor. Symptom: standing water at end of cycle, drain error code. Often resolves at filter clean alone if the pump itself hasn't failed, about 30% of "drain" calls.</li>
      <li><strong>Control board (year 8-12):</strong> $345-$525. Symptoms: cycle won't start, panel display issues, intermittent function loss. Power surge often the trigger.</li>
      <li><strong>Door latch / door switch (year 5-9):</strong> $145-$245. The latch is what tells the controls the door is closed; failure causes the dishwasher to refuse to start.</li>
      <li><strong>Spray arm (year 6-10):</strong> $125-$215. Hard water deposits clog spray arm ports; sometimes mechanical wear cracks the arm itself.</li>
      <li><strong>Heating element (year 8-12):</strong> $185-$285. Symptom: wet dishes at end of cycle, no heat-dry function.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Most "not cleaning" complaints on KitchenAid dishwashers in LA's hard-water territories (especially the Inland Empire and Pasadena) trace to filter neglect rather than mechanical failure. We always inspect and clean the filter assembly on every dishwasher diagnostic visit, about 40% of "broken dishwasher" calls resolve at the filter clean step at the cost of just the diagnostic.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 RANGE / WALL OVEN -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">04, KitchenAid range &amp; wall oven repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">KitchenAid ranges, wall ovens, cooktops, Even-Heat technology.</h2>

    <p class="lead">KitchenAid's range and oven lineup spans entry-tier electric ranges through Pro Line dual-fuel professional ranges, with double wall ovens and cooktops in between. Even-Heat true convection is the platform feature that distinguishes KitchenAid from standalone Whirlpool ranges.</p>

    <p>Common KitchenAid models we service: <strong>KODE507ESS</strong> (30-inch double wall oven, Even-Heat true convection, one of the most-installed wall ovens in LA renovation kitchens), <strong>KOSE500EWH</strong> (combination oven with Even-Heat preferential heating in white finish), <strong>KFGC558JSS</strong> and similar KFGC commercial-style ranges, <strong>KFDC558JSS</strong> dual-fuel premium ranges, plus the KCED induction cooktop family.</p>

    <p>Service tree:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Bake or broil element open (year 8-12):</strong> $185-$285. Most common no-heat repair. Element ohms-out test confirms in 5 minutes.</li>
      <li><strong>Convection fan motor failure (year 8-12):</strong> $245-$385. Symptom: convection cycles run cold, fan doesn't spin, or audible bearing noise from the rear of the oven.</li>
      <li><strong>Oven temperature sensor (F-codes):</strong> $145-$215. F1, F2, F3 codes typically indicate sensor open, short, or out-of-range; sensor swap resolves.</li>
      <li><strong>Door hinge / door wear (year 8-12 on heavy-door units):</strong> $185-$285. Premium-tier doubles have heavier doors that stress the hinge over time.</li>
      <li><strong>Surface igniter on gas units:</strong> $145-$215. Most-common gas range repair across all brands; KitchenAid is no exception.</li>
      <li><strong>Door latch motor on self-cleaning models:</strong> $195-$285. Stuck-locked or stuck-unlocked symptoms.</li>
      <li><strong>Control board:</strong> $345-$525. Last-resort diagnostic after other components ruled out.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>On KODE/KOSE double-oven configurations, the upper and lower ovens are independent, when one oven fails (typically a bake element going open), the other often still works perfectly. We replace just the failed element rather than recommending a full unit swap.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 STAND MIXER -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">05, KitchenAid stand mixer repair</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">KitchenAid stand mixer service, Artisan, Professional, Pro Line. The unique repair angle nobody else fully covers.</h2>

    <p>KitchenAid stand mixers are 15+ year kitchen anchors. Across our service mix, we get calls weekly from Westside, Sherman Oaks, Pasadena, and Newport Beach kitchens where the family Artisan or Pro Line has been in heavy use since the 2000s and is starting to show wear. Most appliance shops in LA either don't service stand mixers or refer them out to electronics repair. We do.</p>

    <p>Three KitchenAid stand mixer architectures, each with predictable service items:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Artisan series (KSM150, KSM160, KSM192, KSM195), tilt-head, 5-quart bowl, 325W motor.</strong> Most-common home stand mixer. Service tree: <em>worm gear failure</em> at year 5-15 depending on use intensity (the brass gear that drives the planetary action, wears mechanically, OEM replacement $145-$245); <em>speed control board</em> ($125-$215, symptoms: speed inconsistency or motor not engaging); <em>motor brushes</em> on older units ($95-$165).</li>
      <li><strong>Professional series (KSM7990, KSM7990WH, KSM7990FBQ), bowl-lift, 7-quart bowl, 1.3 HP motor.</strong> Heavier-duty home tier. Same worm gear and speed control patterns as Artisan but with bowl-lift mechanism, the <em>bowl-lift pin</em> is an additional service item ($85-$145 replacement), as is the lift handle adjustment for units that won't lock in place.</li>
      <li><strong>Pro Line / Pro 600 / Pro 5 Plus (KP26M1X, KV25G0X), bowl-lift, 6-quart bowl, 575W motor.</strong> The pro-styled tier. Same service architecture as Professional but with phase control board ($125-$215 if speed-skipping during a recipe) and slightly different bowl-lift mechanism.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Diagnostic on a KitchenAid stand mixer: we test the worm gear by rotating the planetary head by hand with the unit unplugged (a worn or stripped gear has visible play); we test the speed control by running the motor through all speeds and noting any inconsistency or skipping; we inspect motor brushes on older units for length and contact. Most repairs are 30-60 minutes including diagnostic and we use OEM KitchenAid parts only, third-party gears are commonly available but they don't have the same brass alloy specification and they fail faster.</p>
  </div>
</section>

